Hey everyone! I was trying to deploy a contract on devnet with config as 
```
"devnet": {
      "url": "https://proxy.devnet.minaexplorer.com/graphql",
      "keyPath": "keys/devnet.json",
      "feepayerKeyPath": "/home/[USERNAME]/.cache/zkapp-cli/keys/deployer.json",
      "feepayerAlias": "deployer",
      "fee": "0.1",
      "smartContract": "FundMe"
    }
```

Running `zk deploy` works till creating the verification key for the contract but later crashes with
```
Error: getAccount: Could not find account for public key [MY PUBLIC ADDRESS]
Graphql endpoint: https://proxy.devnet.minaexplorer.com/graphql
Error: getAccount: Could not find account for public key [MY PUBLIC ADDRESS]
Graphql endpoint: https://proxy.devnet.minaexplorer.com/graphql
```
I do have funds on devnet (About 48 MINA). Any help is appreciated! Thanks : )
@br0wnD3v , a scammer tried to approach you. We don't have a support system!
Yeah I had a hunch
Additional info : Was able to deploy to berkeley just fine.
make sure you have funds on feepayerKey: /home/[USERNAME]/.cache/zkapp-cli/keys/deployer.json
Yeah sir, I do have MINA on that account too
can you share your deploy.ts?
Hey @br0wnD3v, you can't deploy a zkApp to devnet. Devnet is the same code base as mainnet. It doesn't support zkApps
Good one
oh lol my bad
The testnet with zkApps is "berkeley" https://berkeley.minaexplorer.com/
Yeah I was able to go through Berkeley just fine
just thought id use devnet this time xD
